results.name: Number of proper divisors of n that are nonabundant (A263837).
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000
example: The seven proper divisors of 24 are 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 12. All except 12 are nonabundant (in A263837), thus a(24) = 6.
xref: Differs from A032741 for the first time at n=24.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Nov 14 2017
